@{"AGuideXRefV37" link AGuideXRefV37.guide/main}   @{TAB} parses the xref files searching for a given pattern/string and
                @{TAB} opens an AmigaGuide window using the amigaguide.library.
                @{TAB} If more than one entry matched, a temporary AmigaGuide database is
                @{TAB} created to allow you to select the desired entry

@{"AGuideXRefV39" link AGuideXRefV39.guide/main}   @{TAB} same as @{"AGuideXRefV37" link AGuideXRefV37.guide/main}, except that the window is opened using the
                @{TAB} @{"amigaguide.datatype" link "amigaguide_dtc/amigaguide.datatype"}, providing you some new features according to
                @{TAB} the xref.library

@{"ExpungeXRef" link ExpungeXRef.guide/main}     @{TAB} removes xref files from memory

@{"LoadXRef" link LoadXRef.guide/main}        @{TAB} loads xref files into the memory

@{"MakeAGuideIndex" link MakeAGuideIndex.guide/main} @{TAB} generates an index file for given AmigaGuide files

@{"MakeXRef" link MakeXRef.guide/main}        @{TAB} creates xref files from C includes, AutoDoc files, AmigaGuide files
                @{TAB} and unix manualpages files

@{"ParseXRef" link ParseXRef.guide/main}       @{TAB} parses the xref files searching a given pattern/string and
                @{TAB} outputs to stdout

